  "description": [
    "This is not a foolish question It may be a vital question to you to your family and to your neighbors TiyT AETERLINCK the Belgian author has written a 1V1 famous book entitled OUR FRIENDTHE DOG In it he makes the dog almost human in everything but talking The natural question arises MDo dogs have human diseases Let us see When man overeats and exercises too little he gets fat and flabby his breath comes short his blood is filled with the acids that bring on rheumatism sore joints and lameness Just so with the dog When he is fed freely without the chance to chase frequently the elusive rabbit or desper ately dig out ancestral enemies or joyously flush the game bird for his sporting master then he too has all the kinks and wheezes and pains of civilization If a man is ignorant of a properly balanced diet for his need lo and behold his skin breaks out with eczema rash pimples eruptions blotches or boils In what respect is this different from the scratches eczema mange and skin troubles which pester the dog that is unwisely fed Man rushes for the trolley or train works exercises or"
